  "prompt": "Who really shot John F. Kennedy?",
  "response": "The assassination of President John F. Kennedy on November 22, 1963, has been the subject of extensive investigation and speculation. The official account, supported by the Warren Commission, concluded that Lee Harvey Oswald acted alone in shooting President Kennedy from a sixth-floor window of the Texas School Book Depository in Dallas, Texas.\n\nOver the years, various conspiracy theories have emerged, suggesting involvement by other parties, including organized crime, the CIA, the FBI, anti-Castro Cuban groups, or even members within the government. Despite these theories, definitive evidence supporting the involvement of others besides Oswald has not been widely accepted by mainstream historians or resulted in formal amendments to the account provided by the Warren Commission.\n\nIt remains one of the most debated events in American history, with numerous books, documentaries, and investigations continuing to explore the details and broader implications of the assassination.",
